Lets assume that we have char map like

\ 0 1 2

0 x a b

1 c b b

and we have to find "abbbc"

as you can see, we can find "abbbc" by visiting 

(0, 1) -> (0, 2) -> (1, 2) -> (1, 1) -> (1, 0) [assuming top left index is (0, 0)]

but following your code, you first visit down, so (1, 1) had marked as visit so you cannot find "abbbc"

to fix this, you have reset visited mark when finish recursion.

```
        if(i!=m-1&&board[i+1][j]==word[k]&&vis[i+1][j]==0)
        {
            vis[i+1][j]=1;
            dfs(board,i+1,j,m,n,word,k+1);
            vis[i+1][j]=0; // this should add to every direction.
        }
```


also, as i mentioned at first, in exist function, you should reset visit map when calling dfs


time limit.


