Answer:
The types of the properties are clearly defined as ```
[PreviousLocations]```
, so you don't need to cast the types except in the filter line. The format string is supposed to be ```
locationName == %@```
.

```
func updateSearchResultsForSearchController(searchController: UISearchController)
{
  let searchPredicate = NSPredicate(format: "locationName == %@", searchController.searchBar.text!)
  filteredPreviousLocations = (previousLocation as NSArray).filteredArrayUsingPredicate(searchPredicate)
  self.tableView.reloadData()
}
