also with printed the approximation error variable final value (abs sum of difference between solution's and input TDoA times in seconds) ... and ```
pos0,pos```
 values...
Beware even this is not fully safe as it has blind spots ...  The receivers should not be at the same altitude and also maybe even not distributed evenly on circle because that can cause the TDoA duplicates...
In case you got additional info (like know that ```
pos0```
 is at ground and have the terrain map) then it might be possible to do this with 3 receivers where the z coordinate will not be approximated anymore but computed from ```
x,y```
 instead...
